                                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[How to Disable YouTube Shorts]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/898096/how-to-disable-youtube-shorts/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mahesh Makvana]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/52861698307_35784b1ef8_o.jpg" length="155984" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[YouTube]]></category><category><![CDATA[features]]></category><category><![CDATA[Cord Cutting]]></category><category><![CDATA[YouTube Shorts]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Kind of.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Not a big fan of YouTube's short-form videos in your feed and want to get rid of them? Unfortunately, there's no longer an official method to turn off <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/720355/what-is-youtube-shorts-and-is-it-a-true-tiktok-competitor/" target="_blank">YouTube Shorts</a>, and while workarounds to hide them stopped working, you do have a few ways to block or otherwise see fewer Shorts. We'll show you how on iPhone, Android phone, and desktop computer.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 13:15:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/898096/how-to-disable-youtube-shorts/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Arduino Reveals Uno Q Board With Debian Linux, and a Qualcomm Acquisition]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/arduino-reveals-uno-q-board-with-linux-support-and-a-qualcomm-acquisition/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Corbin Davenport]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/arduino-uno-q.jpg" length="374" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Qualcomm]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            There's a new Arduino board on the way to compete with Raspberry Pi, and the company is being absorbed into Qualcomm.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Arduino boards are a popular choice for DIY electronics projects and embedded devices, especially in cases where a Raspberry Pi board or other single-board computer isn’t ideal. Now, the Arduino company has plans to be acquired by Qualcomm, while also revealing a new Uno Q board powered by Qualcomm hardware.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 13:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/arduino-reveals-uno-q-board-with-linux-support-and-a-qualcomm-acquisition/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[12 New Prime Video Shows and Movies to Watch for October 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/new-prime-video-shows-and-movies-to-watch-october-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Chris Snellgrove]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/prime-video-logo-and-a-popcorn-bucket-next-to-it.png" length="3387" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[month]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Prime Video is absolutely brimming with tricks and treats this month. And here are the tastiest new shows and movies for you to bite into!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p><a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/video/prime?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2017113&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Fnew-prime-video-shows-and-movies-to-watch-october-2025%2F&asc_campaign=Feed" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Prime Video</a> is a streaming service always brimming with great content. And not just old favorites, either. Each month brings with it plenty of killer TV and movie premieres for anyone hungry for something new to watch.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 13:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/new-prime-video-shows-and-movies-to-watch-october-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[10 New Movies to Watch on Netflix in October 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/new-netflix-movies-to-watch-october-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[T.M. Amrita]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/07/3d-netflix-logo-on-a-dark-reflective-surface-surrounded-by-swirling-red-film-strips-in-a-cinematic-setting.png" length="988" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Streaming]]></category><category><![CDATA[ Movies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Netflix]]></category><category><![CDATA[month]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Streaming]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Spooky season is here, and so are new movies on Netflix.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Settle into a cozy fall with your popcorn and warm drinks as <a href="https://www.howtogeek.com/everything-coming-to-netflix-october-2025/" target="_blank">Netflix's fresh new releases</a> hit your watchlist. October is a great month for streaming, with several films, shows, documentaries, and old titles coming to the streaming platform.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 12:01:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/new-netflix-movies-to-watch-october-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Protect Your Family's Health This Prime Day With Waterdrop Filters]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/protect-your-familys-health-this-prime-day-with-waterdrop-filters/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sponsored]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/09/k6-1.jpg" length="172" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><category><![CDATA[Smart Home]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            This post is sponsored by Waterdrop Filter
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
