                                            A Razer keyboard that's better before you use customization software.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>The <a href="https://www.amazon.com/Razer-BlackWidow-HyperSpeed-Wireless-Swappable/dp/B0FD5276Z6?tag=hotoge-20&ascsubtag=UUhtgUeUpU2017092&asc_refurl=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.howtogeek.com%2Frazer-blackwidow-v3-tenkeyless-hyperspeed-review%2F&asc_campaign=Authority" rel="noopener noreferrer sponsored nofollow" target="_blank" class="norewrite noskim">Razer BlackWidow V4 Tenkeyless HyperSpeed</a> is your archetypal mass-production mechanical keyboard. It has components of a reliable quality at a fair price, but cuts a few noticeable corners to get there. Put otherwise, this keyboard is unremarkably good enough, and that might be okay for the right person.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 10:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/razer-blackwidow-v3-tenkeyless-hyperspeed-review/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Best October Amazon Prime Deals of 2025]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/amazon-october-prime-day-2025/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Kris Henges]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/amazon-logo-with-a-stack-of-shipping-boxes-in-front-set-against-an-orange-and-blue-background.png" length="1126" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Hobbies]]></category><category><![CDATA[Amazon Prime Day 2025]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Get your holiday shopping done early!
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>Amazon's Big Deal Days sales event features deep discounts on a wide range of products, including laptops, phones, and more. We've rounded up the best deals so you don't need to search for them.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Tue, 07 Oct 2025 10:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/amazon-october-prime-day-2025/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Your CD and DVD Collection Is Slowly Destroying Itself]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/your-cd-and-dvd-collection-is-slowly-destroying-itself/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Sydney Butler]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/shutterstock_1608838582.jpg" length="195" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Audio/Video]]></category><category><![CDATA[LaCie Rugged Mini External Hard Drive]]></category><category><![CDATA[physical media]]></category><category><![CDATA[DVD]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            When's the last time you checked in on your collection?
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>I love physical media, you love physical media. Physical media is awesome, and generally just better than digital streaming or downloads, if a little bit less convenient. </p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 06 Oct 2025 22:00:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/your-cd-and-dvd-collection-is-slowly-destroying-itself/</guid></item>                                                                <item><title><![CDATA[Is Your Pixel Hiding Notifications on the Lock Screen? This Setting Is to Blame]]></title><link>https://www.howtogeek.com/pixel-hiding-notifications-how-to-fix/</link><dc:creator><![CDATA[Kabir Jain]]></dc:creator><enclosure url="https://static0.howtogeekimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/a-google-pixel-lock-screen-showing-a-notification-card-with-a-red-warning-sign.png" length="2369" type="image/jpeg"/><category><![CDATA[Android]]></category><category><![CDATA[Google Pixel]]></category><description><![CDATA[
                                            Google giveth, Google taketh away.
                                        ]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[
                                                                                                                                    <p>When I set up my Pixel 10 for the first time, I was pretty happy with how smooth the process was. But then I hit something that didn’t feel right. My lock screen was only showing one notification in full, while the rest were shrunk down into a row of tiny app icons. This new compact style is part of Android 16 QPR1, which the Pixel 10 ships with by default, and it’s designed to keep things tidy.</p>                    ]]></content:encoded><pubDate>Mon, 06 Oct 2025 21:00:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.howtogeek.com/pixel-hiding-notifications-how-to-fix/</guid></item></channel>
